<br>
One of my gripes with the dye is that it dyes the slot and not the item.  Maybe they did this so everyone would have to buy LoY to be able to play with the dyes... I don't know.  But honestly, I really don't want every single robe I have to be the same color when I put it in the chest slot.<br>
<br>
Also I'm not totally sure about how it works when you put another robe in... I only did it for a second.  But I believe the color that showed up when I selected 'Dye' option in inventory, was the numbers for the Emp robe and not my old black robe that was currently in the check slot... (Yes I dyed the emp robe, then dyed it back to blue... now all robes have the emp robe numbers) Therefore I can't change my black robe, back to it's original color because I didn't expect all of them to dye back to the color of my emp robe.  &lt;--- I really don't like this<br>
<br>
I guess the point is, please give us a Reset option to dye specific items back to their original colors at no cost (regent cost).  Because it dyes slots and not the item. Or change it to dying the item and not the slot... IMO would make it a lot nicer.<br>
<br>
